About

   [http://sass-lang.com/]Sass is an extension of CSS that adds power and
   elegance to the basic language. It allows you to use variables, nested
   rules, mixins, inline imports, and more, all with a fully
   CSS-compatible syntax. Sass helps keep large stylesheets
   well-organized, and get small stylesheets up and running quickly.

   Sass has two syntaxes. The new main syntax (as of Sass 3) is known as
   "SCSS" (for "Sassy CSS"), and is a superset of CSS's syntax. This means
   that every valid CSS stylesheet is valid SCSS as well. SCSS files use
   the extension .scss.

   The second, older syntax is known as the indented syntax (or just
   "Sass"). Inspired by Haml's terseness, it's intended for people who
   prefer conciseness over similarity to CSS. Instead of brackets and
   semicolons, it uses the indentation of lines to specify blocks.
   Although no longer the primary syntax, the indented syntax will
   continue to be supported. Files in the indented syntax use the
   extension .sass.

Getting Started

     * [http://sass-lang.com/guide]Official Sass and SCSS Guide - Official
       Sass and SCSS guide.
     * [http://tutorialzine.com/2016/01/learn-sass-in-15-minutes/]Tutorial
       zine - Learn SASS in 15 minutes tutorial.
     * [https://www.codecademy.com/learn/learn-sass]Codecademy - Learn
       Sass with Codecademy.
     * [https://www.lynda.com/SASS-training-tutorials/1435-0.html]Lynda -
       Learn how to use Sass, from beginner basics to advanced techniques,
       with online video tutorials taught by industry experts.
     * [http://sass-lang.com/documentation/file.SASS_REFERENCE.html]Offici
       al Sass and SCSS Reference - Official Sass and SCSS Documentation
       Reference.
     * [https://www.sitepoint.com/sass-reference/]SitePoint Sass and SCSS
       Reference - SitePoint Sass and SCSS reference.

Sass vs SCSS

     * [https://www.sitepoint.com/whats-difference-sass-scss/]SitePoint -
       What's the difference between Sass and SCSS?
     * [http://thesassway.com/editorial/sass-vs-scss-which-syntax-is-bette
       r]The Sass Way - Which syntax is better?
     * [http://stackoverflow.com/questions/5654447/whats-the-difference-be
       tween-scss-and-sass]Stack Overflow - What's the difference between
       SCSS and Sass?

Frameworks

     * [https://github.com/twbs/bootstrap]Bootstrap 4 - Bootstrap version
       4, the most popular HTML, CSS, and JS framework for developing
       responsive, mobile first projects on the web.
     * [https://github.com/twbs/bootstrap-sass]Bootstrap-sass - Official
       Sass port of Bootstrap 2 and 3.
     * [https://github.com/zurb/foundation-sites]Foundation for Sites -
       The most advanced responsive front-end framework in the world.
       Quickly create prototypes and production code for sites that work
       on any kind of device.
     * [http://dropbox.github.io/scooter/]Scooter - SCSS framework built
       to provide base styles, CSS components, and rapid static
       prototyping for Dropbox.
     * [http://sierra-library.github.io/]Sierra - Micro SCSS library to
       help you build websites, without all the arbitrary selectors.
     * [http://trykickoff.com/]Kickoff - Kickoff is a lightweight
       front-end framework for creating scalable, performant and
       responsive sites.
     * [https://bkzl.github.io/hocus-pocus/]Hocus-Pocus - Universal and
       lightweight stylesheet starter kit that focuses on base html
       elements and typography.
     * [http://materializecss.com/]Materialize - Modern responsive
       front-end framework based on Material Design.
     * [https://github.com/jgthms/bulma]Bulma - Modern CSS framework based
       on Flexbox.
     * [https://www.iotacss.com/]iotaCSS - Open source Sass-based OOCSS
       framework built for scale.
     * [http://minicss.org/]mini.css - Minimal, responsive, style-agnostic
       CSS framework.
     * [https://avalanche.oberlehner.net/]avalanche - Framework for
       building the foundation for a package based CSS workflow.

Libraries and Mixins

Grid

     * [http://csswizardry.com/csswizardry-grids/]csswizardry-grids -
       Simple, fluid, nestable, flexible, Sass-based, responsive grid
       system.
     * [http://gridlex.devlint.fr/]Gridlex - Flexbox grid system.
     * [http://neat.bourbon.io/]Neat - Lightweight semantic grid framework
       built with Sass.
     * [http://flexible.gs/install/scss]SCSS Flexible Grid System - SCSS
       flexible grid system.
     * [http://flexible.gs/install/sass]Sass Flexible Grid System - Sass
       flexible grid system.
     * [https://github.com/oddbird/susy]Susy - Responsive layout toolkit
       for Sass.
     * [http://colourgarden.net/avalanche]Avalanche - Lightweight,
       responsive, Sass-based, BEM-syntax grid system.
     * [http://daneden.github.io/Toast/]Toast - Flexible and lightweight
       grid framework from the creator of
       [https://daneden.github.io/animate.css/]animate.css.
     * [https://github.com/mojotech/jeet]Jeet - Simple fractional grid
       system for Sass and Stylus.
     * [http://necolas.github.io/griddle/]Griddle - Extremely flexable CSS
       grid constructor.
     * [https://lucasgruwez.github.io/waffle-grid/]Waffle Grid - Easy to
       use flexbox grid system.

Media Queries

     * [http://include-media.com/]include-media - Simple, elegant and
       maintainable media queries.
     * [http://paranoida.github.io/sass-mediaqueries/]Sass MediaQueries -
       Collection of useful media queries mixins for Sass (including iOS
       devices, TVs and more).
     * [https://github.com/sass-mq/sass-mq]Sass MQ - Sass mixin that helps
       you compose media queries in an elegant way.
     * [https://github.com/at-import/breakpoint]Breakpoint - Breakpoint
       makes writing media queries in Sass super simple.
     * [https://github.com/Dan503/mq-scss]mq-scss - An extreamly powerful
       but easy to use Sass media query mixin.

Color

     * [https://github.com/heygrady/scss-blend-modes]scss-blend-modes -
       Using standard color blending functions in Sass.
     * [http://brand-colors.com/]brand-colors - 1100+ collection of
       popular brand colors available in Sass, Less, Stylus and CSS.
     * [https://github.com/yeun/open-color]Open color - Open color is a
       color scheme for UI design. Available in CSS, SCSS, LESS, Stylus,
       Adobe library, Photoshop/Illustrator swatches and Sketch palette.
     * [https://github.com/xi/sass-planifolia]sass-planifolia - Advanced
       color manipulation and contrast calculation in vanilla Sass.

Typography

     * [https://sassline.com/]Sassline - Set text on the web to a baseline
       grid with Sass & rems using a responsive modular-scale.
     * [https://github.com/zellwk/typi]Typi - Sass mixin to make
       responsive typography easy.
     * [https://github.com/hiulit/Sassy-Gridlover]Sassy-Gridlover - Super
       easy to use Sass mixins to establish a typographic system with
       modular scale and vertical rhythm. Based on the Gridlover app.
     * [http://kyleshevlin.github.io/shevy/]Shevy - Typography made easy.
       A vertical rhythm library.

Animation

     * [https://github.com/jorenvanhee/sass-burger]Sass Burger - Sass
       mixin for creating animated hamburger icon.
     * [https://matejkustec.github.io/SpinThatShit/]SpinThatShit - Set of
       SCSS mixins for single element loaders and spinners.
     * [https://github.com/geoffgraham/animate.scss]Animate.scss - Port of
       Dan Eden's [https://daneden.github.io/animate.css/]Animate.css for
       SASS.
     * [http://ianlunn.github.io/Hover/]Hover - Collection of CSS3 powered
       hover animated effects to be applied to links, buttons, logos, SVG,
       featured images and so on. Available in CSS, Sass, and LESS.

Miscellaneous

     * [http://bourbon.io/]Bourbon - Simple and lightweight mixin library
       for Sass.
     * [http://lukyvj.github.io/family.scss/]Family.scss - Set of 26 smart
       Sass mixins which will help you to manage the style of
       :nth-child'ified elements, in an easy and classy way.
     * [https://github.com/JohnAlbin/normalize-scss]normalize-scss -
       Sass/Compass version of Normalize.css, a collection of HTML element
       and attribute rulesets to normalize styles across all browsers.
     * [https://github.com/alexwolfe/Buttons]Buttons - CSS button library
       built using Sass and Compass.
     * [https://github.com/modularscale/modularscale-sass]Modular Scale -
       Modular scale calculator built into your Sass.
     * [https://github.com/davidtheclark/scut]Scut - Collection of Sass
       utilities to ease and improve the implementations of common
       style-code patterns.
     * [https://github.com/mastastealth/sass-flex-mixin]Sass flexbox mixin
       - Set of mixins for those who want to mess around with flexbox
       using the native support of current browsers.
     * [https://github.com/josephfusco/angled-edges]Angled Edges - Sass
       mixin for creating angled edges on sections by dynamically encoding
       SVGs.
     * [https://github.com/imulus/retinajs]retina.js - JavaScript, SCSS,
       Sass, Less, and Stylus helpers for rendering high-resolution image
       variants.
     * [http://oddbird.net/open-source/accoutrement/]Sass Accoutrement -
       Accoutrement modules are Sass toolkits that work together to form
       the central configuration of a project. The tools can be used
       individually, or integrated for extra power.
     * [https://github.com/davidkpiano/sassdash]Sassdash - The Sass
       implementation of lodash
       ([http://davidkpiano.github.io/sassdash]API documentation).
     * [http://kylebrumm.com/juice/]Juice - Collection of Sass mixins and
       functions.
     * [https://github.com/salesforce-ux/sass-deprecate]Sass Deprecate -
       Sass mixin that helps managing code deprecation.
     * [https://github.com/lokesh-coder/pretty-checkbox]Pretty checkbox -
       SCSS/CSS library to beautify checkbox and radio buttons.

Style Guides

     * [https://sass-guidelin.es/]Hugo Giraudel's Sass Guidelines -
       Guidelines for writing sane, maintainable and scalable Sass.
     * [https://github.com/bigcommerce/sass-style-guide]BigCommerce Sass
       Coding Guidelines - Guidelines in use at BigCommerce.
     * [https://github.com/airbnb/css]Airbnb Sass and CSS Style Guide -
       Sass and CSS style guide by Airbnb.
     * [https://github.com/dropbox/css-style-guide]Dropbox (S)CSS Style
       Guide - Dropbox's (S)CSS authoring style guide.

